cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with facial expression manipulation in images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) and flow-based methods, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or both. Additionally, the paper involves manipulating facial expressions, which could be considered a graphics problem, leading to the possibility of it being categorized under cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper involves image manipulation, which could also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
